  <festivals><![CDATA[<p><strong>Feast Day of San Costanzo (14 May)</strong></p>
<p>This event celebrates the patron saint of Capri. A procession will start in the piazetta of Capri Town and continue to Marina Grande before the statue is carried back to the cathedral of Santo Stefano.</p>
<p><strong>Feast Day of Saint Anthony (13 June)</strong></p>
<p>Saint Anthony is the patron saint of Anacapri and the whole town is decorated with lights and banners in the week leading up to the event. On the day of the feast, a statue of the saint is carried through the town while residents toss rose petals from above.</p>
<p><strong>Feast Day of Madonna della Libera (12 September)</strong></p>
<p>This traditional religious festival celebrates Madonna della Libera with a procession through the fishing village of Marina Grande before a concert is held in the evening.</p>]]></festivals>
